 {"id":"bd-3bxhj.5","title":"epic(opentui-import): Capability gap closure in FrankenTUI","description":"## Background\nClose real capability gaps in FrankenTUI so migrated apps remain faithful and robust without compatibility shims or technical debt.\n\n## Scope\n- Automated capability-gap detection from translation outcomes and corpus data.\n- Prioritization model (impact x frequency x risk).\n- Runtime/widget/style/layout/text/backend feature additions where required.\n- Reintegration of new capabilities into mapping/planner infrastructure.\n- Unit + E2E regression suites for each introduced capability.\n\n## Success Criteria\n1. Every detected high-impact gap has explicit resolution path (implement, defer with risk, or unsupported).\n2. New capabilities are first-class, tested, and integrated into planner/mapping contracts.\n3. Gap-closure changes do not regress determinism, certification outcomes, or existing demos.\n4. E2E regression suite demonstrates measurable parity improvements on corpus fixtures.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:20.847548969Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-24T22:22:56.238113330Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["feature-parity","ftui","opentui-import"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3bxhj.5","depends_on_id":"bd-3bxhj","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-02-24T21:28:20.847548969Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
